The paper discusses reinforcement learning and policy iteration using classifiers, which are topics commonly associated with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the core sampling problem in evaluating a policy through simulation, which is a common issue in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm that offers improved performance with less computational effort, which is a topic of interest in neural networks (cs.NE).
